<subSubSection pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1436,829,1250]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1009,1034]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</emphasis>
There is a further lot (
<collectionCode box="[527,611,1010,1034]" country="Italy" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mmbj-pfva" name="Museo Civico di Zoologia" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">MCZR</collectionCode>
, unnumbered box) of 1 valve identified as 
<taxonomicName box="[1101,1233,1009,1034]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Lima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pterioida" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subovata">
<emphasis box="[1101,1233,1009,1034]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">L. subovata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by Jeffreys, from Palermo, labelled by Brugnone (“ 
<taxonomicName authority="Jeffr." authorityName="Jeffr." box="[529,759,1045,1070]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Lima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pterioida" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subovata">
<emphasis box="[529,695,1045,1070]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Lima subovata</emphasis>
Jeffr.
</taxonomicName>
from Jeffr.”), and by Jeffreys (“1443 fms. P.”). Monterosato bought Brugnone’s collection after his death (1884), therefore there is no proof that this shell was part of the 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,1082,1106]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">type</typeStatus>
material (but Monterosato has likely studied Brugnone’s collection before acquiring it). However, the morphology of the single valve fits very well the shell features of the 
<typeStatus box="[785,833,1154,1178]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">type</typeStatus>
material, showing that both Monterosato and Jeffreys shared the same view on the species identity (
<taxonomicName authority="Jeffreys, 1876" authorityName="Jeffreys" authorityYear="1876" box="[664,997,1189,1214]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Lima" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pterioida" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subovata">
<emphasis box="[664,829,1189,1214]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Lima subovata</emphasis>
Jeffreys, 1876
</taxonomicName>
, is separately available and has its own 
<typeStatus box="[151,210,1226,1250]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">types</typeStatus>
in 
<collectionCode box="[246,332,1226,1250]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">USNM</collectionCode>
). Recorded by MolluscaBase (2018) as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Monterosato, 1875)" authorityName="Monterosato" authorityYear="1875" baseAuthorityName="Monterosato" baseAuthorityYear="1875" box="[777,1226,1225,1250]" class="Bivalvia" family="Limidae" genus="Limatula" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Pterioida" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subovata">
<emphasis box="[777,986,1225,1250]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Limatula subovata</emphasis>
(Monterosato, 1875)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
